				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Soloing,  what's your motivation?<a name="27211"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 12 04 9:30 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I know why I solo,  I'm LFG or only have 30 minutes to play.  Something along those lines.  What I want to know is what's the motivation for soloing to the exclusion of all else.  I don't mean just bards.  Also druids, necros,  shadow knights and beastlords do it.  I have a BL alt that I play but as I said that's for times when I don't have a lot of time to play or don't feel like constant twisting.  
<br />

<br />
The other night I started a new bard and started AoE kiting.  I got to near level 4 when I started getting tells complaing about me hogging the newbie area in Kelethin.  I logged off when I checked and saw that one of my friends had come online.  After chating about it for a while he told me about being over in LoIO and watching a bard AoE one night.  His group invited the bard to join but he wouldn't.  The bard died twice that night,  before logging off he asked how many levels the bard had gained and he told them he'd gone up one level.  Everyone in the group had a level too.  He didn't see the point in paying for an MMORPG if you're going to play stand alone.  I sort of see the  point.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
