				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Soloing,  what's your motivation?<a name="27229"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 12 04 9:47 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Sometimes I don't feel like the hassles associated with collecting up a group and getting coordinated.
<br />

<br />
Sometimes I have a specific goal in mind and nobody else much wants to work on that -- i.e., chardok faction, etc.
<br />

<br />
Sometimes I just have a little time free.
<br />

<br />
But the #1 reason is that sometimes the people I like to group with aren't online.  I just never do pickup groups anymore.  Just not my thing -- about half the time they work out OK but the other half, there's someone who annoys the h*ll out of me.  I play EQ for fun, and being pestered or annoyed by a random pickup isn't fun.  So I decline to do it. 
<br />

<br />
Still spend easily 80+% of my EQ time grouped, but when I'm not its usually because friends aren't on.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
