				<td colspan="2"><span>I'm pretty much the same as liis.  I start my night in PoN, where I can mindlessly swarm while deciding on my moves for the night.  If I'm super tired, I may just swarm for a bit, inviting friends who are leveling alts to come sit in, or I might put LFG up.  If I decide on grouping, I'll do however many LDoNs etc are wanted, raid if raid is called, and unless it's really late, I'll end up in PoN finishing an AA off.  
<br />

<br />
If I want a change of scenery, I'll hit up an old high level Kunark or Velious zone (such as DN, HS, Seb - I still say you can't beat them for fun zone layout) and bum around.  Sometimes I can drag friends along, sometimes I go solo.  I guess my main motivation is, I want to go NOW, not in 30 minutes or 1 hour or however long it would take to organise a pick up group. I love the fact that if I want to do something, I pretty much can do it.  I may die a lot discovering how, but so long as I feel I'm achieving something, then I don't care. </span></td>
