				<td colspan="2"><span>I solo to let others share in my glory.
<br />

<br />
Just the other night I was soloing in BOT.  Dot Kiting  Brann Militis around the stairs.  When they got down to 20 percent or so, I would run them to the Safe room and let the folks there kill them off for me.  Some of them complained.  WTF, they are sitting there doing nothing, they might as well help me get some exp, they should thank me for giving them a chance to get a skill up in defense.
<br />

<br />
In PoN I like to Charm kite around the hedges or the GY.   It is a great way for people to see me in action.  18 Folks setting up for the hedge maze = 18 folks who need to warm up on 25 banshees and hobgoblins.  And naked folks waiting on corpses to pop at the GY are always FM, so why not use that mana to kill some mobs in my huge tree train?  Again, I rarely get thanked or told what a stud I am.
<br />

<br />
Besides swarm kiting for glory, I also use my bag of tricks to relive the tensions of boring exp grinds.  Nothing livens up a KC group like your mob gating at 10% and bringing back friends right?  Well, with me around, sometimes those mobs gate at 20, 30, even 50%, and they ARENT EVEN CASTERS!!  Giants in BoT can gate too, you wanna see some people become very alert very fast?  Find a Deep south group that &quot;Steals&quot; a Tables/Mid south named.  Garunteed fun and excitement!  I am the BoT avenger, some nights I just run around and gate everything I see just for fun.  If I get spotted, then hey, that is why we have selos and fading memories right?  Selos then run to the nearest group and fade.  Of course, you have to wait till the giants are reeeeal close to fade, otheriwse, the group cant see you in action and comment on how useful and adaptive bards are.</span></td>
